Guide.title: What is Meta?
Guide.Content: On the surface Meta Facebook seems like an extension of virtual reality (VR), where users can interact with each other through a variety of video games and social spaces. Facebook has invested heavily in virtual reality, spending 1.46 billion on the acquisition of Oculus. It looks like the metaverse will take this on a deeper route with the vision of creating a virtual reality space all over the internet. It is not only focused on video games and creating more space on various platforms.

Guide.title: Develop an account.
Guide.Content: Before creating an account, you need to tap 'Settings' on the iPhone or iPad to discover the Meta logo design and then choose 'Develop a new account'.

Guide.title: Fill in your information to register.
Guide.Content: Then enter your last name, first name, email address, date of birth, gender, and password. You must use your real name for your account. After entering all your information, tap 'Register' to go to the next page.
